parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the driver is unable to control the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without the driver's input
often when the brake pedal is depressed
and the engine RPM increases rapidly. The driver may need to shift into neutral or park to regain control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can lead to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control system fails to engage or disengage
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly. The driver may experience difficulty controlling the vehicle
especially when braking or shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body or cruise control cable can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The throttle body or cruise control cable becomes stuck or disconnected
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly. The driver may experience difficulty controlling the vehicle
especially when braking or shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the exhaust pipe to drop to the ground, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: exhaust pipe falls to the ground

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or shift hard, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
